This paper is about optimization algorithms for deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. The paper specifically discusses the convergence proof of the AMSGrad algorithm, which is commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. Additionally, the paper presents experimental results on benchmark datasets, which could also fall under the data science (cs.DS) sub-category.
